rior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/28/03 1:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2834.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Which weapons skills</span><hr size=1> I am currently rolling up a Troll warrior. My question is this:<br>
How important is it to try and max out all weapons skills?? At the higher end game (50+), it seems almost all warriors are using either 1hs or 2hs weapons. I have maxed 1hs and 2hs for my current level (21). Since warriors can use all types of weapons, trying to keep 5 skills maxed would be very difficult. <p>Thoriel Galadrim&lt;BR&gt;<br>
Templar of Tunare&lt;BR&gt;<br>
Tenoray Tuneweaver&lt;BR&gt;<br>
Bard of Bristlebane&lt;BR&gt;<br>
Proud member and GOF of The Royal Knights</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=strikingone>StrikingOne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/28/03 1:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2834.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Which weapons skills</span><hr size=1> All weapons skills.<br>
<br>
Its not that hard to raise em if you want to a couple days raising each one you need at 60 tho. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=196963"><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.theedge.ca/traverc/s1new_sig.jpg" style="border:0;"alt="Touch me, I dare you."/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ragnok>Ragnok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/28/03 2:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2834.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Which weapons skills</span><hr size=1> If you want to be resourceful, its good to have them all maxed (hides his h2h skill number.) If my slower dies, its nice to pull out my 2hb that procs 30% slow, or if im duoing with a cleric its nice to use a snare proc weapon and switch back. Most warriors that have been alive for a few years have basically a utility belt of weapons on them for different occasions. <br>
<br>
True, you could fill the role of a warrior pretty well and only have 1hs maxed, but its all about whether or not you want to take the time to round out your abilities. For me its about trying to make my warrior more than what verant really wants it to be /shrug<br>
<br>
Rag <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eoden01>Eoden01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/28/03 3:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2834.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Which weapons skills</span><hr size=1> seeing as you never know what gear you are going to score at the end of the day it pays to keep them all as high as you can.  As you go up levels and each level takes longer to complete you'll find you have plenty of time to use a piecer or 1hb off hand while maintaining a 1hs in primary.<br>
<br>
Would suck if it was your turn to be awarded primal (prismatic or whatever it is these days) and the next one to drop was a warhammer when your 1hb skill is only 10. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50585" target="top">Eoden</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Halfelven Warlord<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg" target="top">The Tribunal</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daleb123>Daleb123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/28/03 6:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2834.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Which Weapons</span><hr size=1> You're a Warrior - your purpose in life is to stand toe-to-toe with your enemies and fight them with melee weapons. Why in the world would you want to limit your selection?<br>
<br>
The truth is that with so many players favoring slashing weapons, you can purchase comparable blunt weapons for a fraction of the price. My Warrior's best weapon is 2HB - a comparable 2HS would have cost 3 times the price. My Ranger's best weapon is 2HB - a comparable slashing weapon would have cost almost 5 times the price.<br>
<br>
Learn them all, so that you always have the best available. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farlanderb>FarlanderB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/28/03 6:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2834.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Which Weapons</span><hr size=1> Fellow once told me that since our epic is 1hs-2hs based, THOSE are the weapon skills that were intended for us and he wasn't going to bother with the blunt or piercing weapons that we have out there. Few days later his guild got him a nice 1hb weapon, and he complained to me that he was having aggro problems in Valor because his 1hb skill was so low, and his new weapon wasn't proc'ing. All I could do was laugh.<br>
<br>
Max them all. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Farlander - 65 Overlord of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guild-legerdemain.com">Legerdemain</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trylerc>trylerc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/03 6:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2834.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   yep</span><hr size=1> I've heard it said a million times and it's still as true as it gets. Max em all. You don't have to be anal like me and force archery, throwing, and H2H to max, but the fab 5 (1hs, 2hs, 1hb, 2hb, peircing) are essential in my eyes.<br>
<br>
Take a lvl 65 wizard and strip him of his gear...he can still deal out an INCREDIBLE amount of damage, although his mana pool will prevent him from doing it for a long time. Take a lvl 65 warrior and strip his gear and what kind of damage will HE be able to do? My point is simply, we ARE our equipment.<br>
<br>
By shutting out your ability to use certain weapons you make yourself less versatile and less able to deal with certain situations effectively. If I had an ensnaring whip and no 1hs skill then it is essentially useless to me. But if my skill was 250 them I become a warrior who can snare. If you can dig it. Max them all. You're shortchanging yourself if you don't.<br>
<br>
I remember people saying that anything other than 1hs was a joke. Look at the new positive ratio 2HS drops from PoP. Funny, I don't hear anyone knocking 2hs anymore. Maybe the weapon that makes these look like toys will be 2hb.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
stand and be true<br>
<br>
rexiant<br>
